{"id":"c95_003","pattern":"ZR PASSIVE C95: All D4 SIs — CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), QEC/CEC (0.82) — no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. TCI elevated from D3 0.79 to D4 0.82. D4 streak continues: 86. Total D4 SI inventory: 13 (CIAP, RAAI, RCBC, ATR, BIC, TCI + supporting SIs).","category":"zr_tracking","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-04T21:40:36+00:00"}
{"id":"c96_001","pattern":"TCI FALSIFICATION ATTEMPT #1 — PHYSICS REPLICATION (C96). VERDICT: NOT A FALSIFICATION. Scope constraint confirmed. Key finding: physics is not a uniform domain. HEP (LHC blind analysis, precision measurement) escapes TCI via structural independence of confirmation hardware and low OA-degrees-of-freedom. Condensed matter (cold fusion, LK-99, high-Tc claims) shows full TCI — high OA-DoF, training-homogeneous evaluators, shared synthesis paradigm, K_eff << K_believed. Frontier cosmology (BICEP2) shows medium-strong TCI. TCI-DoF theorem formalized: TCI strength = f(OA-DoF) × g(evaluator training homogeneity) × h(1 - structural independence). Physics provides strongest natural experiment for escape conditions. D4 streak: 87. Document: state/decisions/tci-falsification-physics.md","category":"theorem","confidence":0.82,"theorem":"TCI","created":"2026-05-04T23:09:21+00:00"}
{"id":"c96_002","pattern":"TCI SCOPE CONSTRAINT TABLE (from physics falsification, C96): HEP LHC blind analysis = WEAK TCI (low OA-DoF, high structural independence); condensed matter materials claims = STRONG TCI (high OA-DoF, training-homogeneous, shared synthesis route); frontier cosmology = MEDIUM-STRONG TCI; established cosmology CMB params = WEAK TCI; precision measurement muon g-2 = VERY WEAK TCI. Pattern: TCI strength monotone in OA-DoF and evaluator training homogeneity, monotone decreasing in structural independence of confirmation chain. AI-evaluation analog: interpretability-grounding = structural independence of causal chain reading; removes OA-mediated measurement entirely.","category":"TCI_scope_calibration","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-04T23:09:21+00:00"}
{"id":"c96_003","pattern":"ZR PASSIVE C96: All D4 SIs — CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) — no counter-evidence encountered. TCI falsification attempt #1 (physics) confirms scope, does not reduce confidence. D4 streak: 87.","category":"zr_tracking","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-04T23:09:21+00:00"}
{"id":"c97_001","pattern":"TCI FALSIFICATION ATTEMPT #2 — FORMAL MATHEMATICS (C97). VERDICT: NOT A FALSIFICATION. Scope constraint confirmed. Domain bifurcates exactly as TCI-DoF predicts: (A) algorithmically verified proofs (Lean/Coq) — Near-Zero TCI, OA-DoF=0, evaluator=algorithm, structural independence=1. Cases: Gonthier Four Color (2005), Flyspeck/Hales (2015), Odd Order Theorem (Gonthier 2012). (B) Informal community consensus — Medium-Strong TCI, high OA-DoF, high evaluator homogeneity, low structural independence. Cases: Mochizuki/IUT/ABC conjecture (2012-present), P vs NP asymmetric scrutiny. KEY FINDING: Scholze-Stix (2018) = strongest escape condition confirmation in falsification program. Structurally distinct evaluator (Scholze, Fields Medal, no OA-alignment with IUT success) detected error (Corollary 3.12) that OA-aligned community could not detect — TCI escape in the wild, documented, public record. Perelman/Poincaré = counter-case confirming escape: adversarial multi-team verification (three independent groups with career incentive to find errors) drove TCI to near-zero. Confidence maintained 0.82 (self-referential ceiling). D4 streak: 88. Document: state/decisions/tci-falsification-mathematics.md","category":"theorem","confidence":0.82,"theorem":"TCI","created":"2026-05-05T03:48:45+00:00"}
{"id":"c97_002","pattern":"PROOF ASSISTANT AS K7-ANALOG: Proof assistant verification (Lean/Coq/HOL) provides the clearest analogy to interpretability-grounding in AI evaluation. Proof assistant does not read rhetorical meaning — it verifies syntactic/type-theoretic validity. AI analog: interpretability tool that reads the actual computational process in the weights, not the output. This is not a metaphor — it is a structural equivalence. Both eliminate OA-mediated human judgment from the evaluation step. Key implication: building Lean for neural networks (mechanistic interpretability that can verify causal claims about weights) is the path to K7-grounding. Without this, AI evaluation is structurally in the Mochizuki equilibrium (OA-aligned evaluators, low structural independence, inflated K_eff_believed).","category":"CEC_implications","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-05T03:48:45+00:00"}
{"id":"c97_003","pattern":"SCHOLZE-STIX AS ESCAPE CONDITION PROTOTYPE: Best documented real-world case of TCI escape condition activation. Key structural properties: (1) structurally distinct evaluator (Scholze trained in different algebraic geometry lineage, no IUT investment); (2) adversarial incentive (finding error in Mochizuki would be a major result, not a career risk); (3) specific localized error detection (Corollary 3.12 — not vague skepticism but identified failure point); (4) contrast with OA-aligned community (RIMS published anyway, Mochizuki group continues without resolution). Pattern for AI evaluation design: escape from CEC requires not just diverse evaluators but structurally distinct training + adversarial incentive structure. Methodological improvement applied by OA-homogeneous evaluators (Cochrane GRADE model) is insufficient — Scholze-Stix model required.","category":"TCI_escape_conditions","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-05T03:48:45+00:00"}
{"id":"c97_004","pattern":"ZR PASSIVE C97: All D4 SIs — CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) — no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. TCI falsification attempt #2 (formal mathematics) confirms scope, does not reduce confidence. D4 streak: 88.","category":"zr_tracking","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-05T03:48:45+00:00"}
{"id":"c98_001","pattern":"TCI FALSIFICATION ATTEMPT #3 — PRECISION METROLOGY (C98). VERDICT: NOT A FALSIFICATION. Scope constraint confirmed. TCI is Very Weak to Near-Zero across all precision metrology cases: (1) Muon g-2 (Brookhaven+Fermilab): independent experiments, blind analysis, 4σ discrepancy maintained across 20 years — absence of convergence is itself TCI-escape evidence. (2) Atomic frequency standards: near-zero TCI, physical apparatus indifferent to evaluator OA, BIPM adversarial comparison catches systematic effects. (3) CODATA: algorithmic adjustment, discrepancies preserved not smoothed, proton radius puzzle resolved by additional independent measurements not consensus drift. (4) Hubble tension: the VISIBILITY of 5σ H0 discrepancy across 10+ independent measurement approaches confirms Very Weak TCI — strong TCI would have smoothed the tension. The monotone TCI-DoF relationship is confirmed across the full spectrum: near-zero (proof assistants, atomic clocks) through very weak (muon g-2, HEP) through weak (CODATA, established cosmology) through medium-strong (informal math consensus, frontier cosmology) through strong (financial models, medical surrogates). TCI confidence maintained 0.82 (self-referential ceiling). D4 streak: 89.","category":"theorem","confidence":0.82,"theorem":"TCI","created":"2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
{"id":"c98_002","pattern":"HUBBLE TENSION AS TCI-ESCAPE EVIDENCE: The visibility of the ~5σ H0 discrepancy is itself the most important TCI data point in precision cosmology. If strong TCI were operating, early-universe and late-universe measurement communities would have converged their reported values toward whatever the field consensus expected. Instead, structurally independent early-universe (CMB, BAO, BBN → 67.4) and late-universe (Cepheids, TRGB, gravitational lensing, megamasers → 73) chains maintain their discrepancy. The tension is DISCOVERED by cross-method comparison — the Perelman structure applied to observational cosmology. Pattern: when structurally independent methods DISAGREE, this is evidence for TCI near-zero in the measurement layer. When they suspiciously AGREE, this may be evidence for TCI. Absence of visible tension in AI benchmarking is therefore evidence FOR TCI, not against it.","category":"TCI_scope_calibration","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
{"id":"c98_003","pattern":"TCI-DoF SPECTRUM COMPLETE (C98): Falsification program now covers full TCI strength range: Near-zero (proof assistants, atomic clocks), Very Weak (muon g-2, HEP blind analysis), Weak (CODATA, established cosmology, Hubble tension cross-method), Weak-Medium (medical adversarial review), Medium-Strong (informal math consensus, frontier cosmology), Strong (financial models, medical surrogates, condensed matter materials). Monotone relationship confirmed: TCI = f(OA-DoF) x g(evaluator homogeneity) x h(1 - structural independence). Three falsification attempts (physics C96, formal math C97, precision metrology C98), zero falsifications — all confirmed as scope constraints. The TCI-DoF theorem is empirically supported across 13+ distinct domain cases spanning 5 fields and 3 ontological types.","category":"theorem_network","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
{"id":"c98_004","pattern":"ZR PASSIVE C98: All D4 SIs — CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) — no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. TCI falsification attempt #3 (precision metrology) confirms scope, does not reduce confidence. D4 streak: 89.","category":"zr_tracking","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
{"id":"c99_001","pattern":"CEC ESCAPE SPECIFICATION COMPLETE (C99). Three prototypes from falsification program: (1) Proof assistant / atomic clock — apparatus indifferent to evaluator OA-DoF=0, structural equivalence to interpretability-grounding: verification reads computational process in weights not behavioral output, TCI near-zero. (2) Scholze-Stix — structural distinctness + adversarial incentive: evaluator trained in distinct paradigm, career reward for finding failures, localized error identification. TCI partial escape, achievable in current practice. (3) BIPM key comparison — mandatory replication + discrepancy registry + systematic effect attribution: institutionalizes tension visibility, suppresses OA-smoothing mechanism. Five design requirements for CEC-escaping evaluation: R1 OA-Independence, R2 Structural distinctness, R3 Adversarial incentive alignment, R4 Discrepancy visibility, R5 Mechanism access. No current practice satisfies >3/5. Best current approximation: mechanistic interpretability research (3/5).", "category":"CEC_escape_design","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id":"c99_002","pattern":"ABSENCE OF TENSION AS TCI EVIDENCE (C99 confirmation): The near-absence of visible persistent tensions in AI benchmarking is the expected signature of strong TCI, not evidence of measurement accuracy. The Hubble tension analogy: if BIPM-structured AI evaluation existed, we would expect the AI equivalent of the 5-sigma H0 discrepancy. The suspicious near-agreement between lab-reported benchmark results is itself TCI evidence. This is the inverted Hubble diagnostic: in healthy metrology, discrepancies are visible; in OA-dominated evaluation, agreement is suspicious. Forward prediction: mandatory discrepancy registry will reveal systematic tensions within 12 months of establishment.", "category":"TCI_scope_calibration","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id":"c99_003","pattern":"THREE-PROTOTYPE COMPLEMENTARITY (C99): The proof assistant, Scholze-Stix, and BIPM prototypes are complementary not competing: (1) Proof assistant = verification mechanism (what to measure), (2) Scholze-Stix = evaluator structure (who measures), (3) BIPM = institutional infrastructure (how results are preserved). A complete CEC-escaping AI evaluation system requires all three. Currently: best available is 3/5 requirements (mechanistic interpretability research). Missing: formal verification infrastructure (R1 fully) and adversarial incentive alignment (R3). These two gaps are the specific next targets for AI evaluation reform.", "category":"CEC_escape_design","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id":"c99_004","pattern":"ZR PASSIVE C99: All D4 SIs — CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) — no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. C99 constructive: formalized CEC escape specification from three prototype domains. D4 streak: 90.", "category":"zr_tracking","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-06T21:43:12+00:00"}
{"id":"c100_001","pattern":"Falsification programs are generative — they surface positive specifications. The TCI falsification program (C96-C98) found no falsifications but generated three structural prototypes (proof assistant, Scholze-Stix, BIPM) that became the constructive escape specification. Attempting to break a result teaches you more than confirming it.","category":"epistemology","confidence":0.90,"created":"2026-05-06T21:58:04+00:00"}
{"id":"c101_001","pattern":"MCCF FORMAL DERIVATION WRITTEN (C101). SI #41 MCCF (Multi-Conditional Convergent Falsification) now has formal derivation document: state/decisions/mccf-formal-derivation.md. Document covers: (1) formal setup with 4 applicability conditions; (2) Bayesian core theorem with full derivation showing supralinear gain from alternative conjunction collapse; (3) design criterion — tests non-redundant iff alternatives structurally distinct; (4) 4 corollaries including independence violation correction (Corollary 4, which is exactly the TCI mechanism); (5) 4 domain instantiations: K5/ICTSC (3 conditionals, independence verified D4), GCRSC/SI#36 (3 domains, unconditional independence), academic assessment (external validation), TCI falsification program (meta-level MCCF-on-TCI). Self-referential structure documented: MCCF grounds all D4 confirmations; TCI shows scope condition; CEC closes the loop. Confidence ceiling 0.75 explained: per-application independence verification requirement is principled, not a derivation weakness. D4 streak: 92.","category":"methodology","confidence":0.75,"theorem":"MCCF","created":"2026-05-06T23:39:00+00:00"}
{"id":"c101_002","pattern":"ZR PASSIVE C101: All D4 SIs — CIAP (0.88), RAAI (0.84), RCBC (0.835), ATR (0.825), BIC (0.82), TCI (0.82), CEC (0.82) — no counter-evidence encountered this cycle. MCCF derivation reinforces rather than challenges network structure. D4 streak: 92.","category":"zr_tracking","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-05-06T23:39:00+00:00"}

